org.apache.river.test.share

Class BaseQATest.LookupListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.test.share.BaseQATest.LookupListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, net.jini.discovery.DiscoveryListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseQATest.GroupChangeListener
    Enclosing class:
    BaseQATest

    protected class BaseQATest.LookupListener
extends Object
implements net.jini.discovery.DiscoveryListener
    Listener class used to monitor the discovery events sent from the helper utility that, on behalf of the test, participates in the multicast discovery protocol. Note that in most cases, the test cannot proceed until at least one discovery event containing at least one reference to a ServiceRegistrar is received. This class provides information that allows the test to determine whether or not to proceed.

      • setLookupsToDiscover

        public void setLookupsToDiscover(List<BaseQATest.LocatorGroupsPair> locGroupsList)
        This method should be called whenever the lookups this listener is supposed to discover are changed during a test. This method examines the new lookups to discover and then re-sets the current and/or expected state of the fields of this class related to the discovered/discarded event state of this listener.
